        <body>
            <p>Re<hi rend="sup">d</hi> Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Herewith I enclose 5$ you will please to give my ap <add>?</add>
                with<lb/> three Dollars. I re<hi rend="sup">d</hi> 75/100 for 12 numbers address to
                F W. my care, this person<lb/> could not afford to pay the amt. of subscription at
                once he paid me 25/100 for each<lb/> 4 numbers, as you have discontinued sending to
                him let it remain so.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I am not aware that you still send to <placeName>Beloit</placeName>.
                I mentioned<lb/> this to my son he has neglected to reply. he will be here soon and
                if he is<lb/>
                <sic>receving</sic> the Occident, he will desire me to settle his a/c. I have
                been<lb/> frequently <sic>disapointed</sic> in not receiving the Weekly Nos.
                regularly on one<lb/> ocassion I was 2 weeks without getting any. There are several
                persons here<lb/> who have met the same <sic>disapointment</sic>. This should be
                    <sic>enquired</sic> after—</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">This Post will bring you a packet for publication. I have
                reason<lb/> to believe the subject will meet yr. approval, and induce you to
                afford<lb/> them a space to print them, as they are arranged, the interest I have
                in<lb/> the subject I seek to advocate, induces me to say, I shall be glad to see
                them on<lb/> record, to continue them in any other manner would render the subject
                unintell<lb/>igible, and in that case it would be better not to insert them at
                all<lb/> I have two more chapt. on the same subject for continuation, they<lb/> will
                occupy less space than these now sent. I will send them on in due<lb/> time for
                publication. Our Family have been residing all the summer in<lb/> the
                    <sic>cuntry</sic>, we have only removed into the city again a few days back.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I shall have now leisure time to <hi rend="underline">copy</hi> what
                I have already written</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">In a private conversation with <persName>Jo. Abraham</persName> who
                is now<lb/>
                <add>פרלם</add> of the <add>?</add>way <add>?</add> he assures me that he has heard
                both the<lb/> Doctors declare that they are opposed to meet any convention they
                admit<lb/> the orthodox have the majority but not the wisdom</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Dr. Wise</persName> is <sic>urgeing</sic> his members to
                build a Temple the seats<lb/> to be made &amp; sold for a family, the Gent. &amp;
                their wives, with their hair uncovered<lb/> and many other improvements <add>?</add>
                will follow the same plan<lb/> the Doctor only is waiting to see the result of
                    <add>?</add> when he will carry<lb/> his plans. The Roof of the <add>?</add>way
                    <add>?</add> requires a new roof with other costly<lb/> improvements which must
                come from the wealthy, and they are the<lb/> majority. It is time that some attempt
                should be made to check those<lb/> unholy proceedings.yours in haste</p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">
                <persName role="author">F Bruel</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
